   "source": [
    "# The Zeeman Effect\n",
    "\n",
    "Zeeman splitting depends on the relative strengths between the externally imposed magnetic field and the internal magnetic field of the atom. There are three regimes of note: the weak-field, the strong-field and the intermediate regime.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Weak-Field Zeeman Effect\n",
    "In the weak-field regime where $ B_ext << B_int $, fine structure dominates and the Zeeman effect acts as a small perturbation on the system.\n",
    "\n",
    "From first-order non-degenerate perturbation theory, the Zeeman correction to the energy is $ E^{1}_{Z} = \\mu_B g_J{} B_{ext} m_{j} $, where $\\mu_B$ is the Bohr magneton and $g_J$ is the LandÃ© g-factor. This factor is given by \n",
    "\n",
    "$$ g_J = 1 + \\frac{j(j+1)-l(l+1)+3/4}{2j(j+1)} .$$\n",
    "\n",
    "The total energy of the system is the sum of the contribution from both the fine-structure corrections and the Zeeman effect."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
   ]
